In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims December 2010 as Critical Infrastructure Protection Month. The article emphasizes the importance of recognizing and protecting the assets, networks, and functions that are essential to the security, economic welfare, public health, and safety of the United States. The Department of Homeland Security leads a national partnership to identify and protect critical infrastructure from hazards or attacks. The proclamation highlights the need to provide information, tools, and resources to areas with critical infrastructure and proposes a plan for renewing and expanding the nation's infrastructure. The article also calls for empowering communities to work with local infrastructure owners and operators to enhance the resilience of physical and cyber infrastructure. The president urges the people of the United States to observe this month with appropriate events and training to enhance national security and resilience.